    <title>Creating a bundle</title>

    <para>
    The next step is the creating of a new module, that is, a new bundle.
    A <emphasis>bundle</emphasis> is a normal jar component with extra manifest headers, 
    while a module defines the dependencies on how a bundle imports and exports the code. 
    At the same time, this module will be the base for any further and future expanding. 
    Again, we select <emphasis>File-New-Project</emphasis>, but now choose 
    <emphasis>maven module</emphasis>.
    
        <figure>
            <title>Creating a bundle - step 1</title>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="img04-create_maven_project_1.png"  scalefit="1" width="100%" contentdepth="100%" />
                </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
        </figure>
    </para>
    
    <para>
    Now we should get the following screen, which we will fill in such a manner:
    
    <programlisting>
    Module Name: panifex-samples-salute-spi
    Parent Project: panifex-samples
    </programlisting>
    
        <figure>
            <title>Creating a bundle - step 2</title>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="img04-create_maven_project_1.png"  scalefit="1" width="100%" contentdepth="100%" />
                </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
        </figure>
    
    </para>
    
    <para>
    After clicking <emphasis>Next</emphasis> we should get this screen:
    
        <figure>
            <title>Creating a bundle - step 1</title>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="img04-create_maven_project_1.png"  scalefit="1" width="100%" contentdepth="100%" />
                </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
        </figure>
    
    As seen from this, type in the following:
    <programlisting>
    Name: panifex-samples-salute-spi
    Packaging: bundle  
    # The rest will be automatically inserted
    </programlisting> 
    </para>
    
    </chapter>